---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="Terms & Disclaimer — Dudela" description="Terms of service and disclaimer for The Dudela Co. — our guides, workshops, coaching, membership, and merch.">
  <Nav />

  <section class="page-hero section-dark">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Terms &amp; Disclaimer</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">Last updated {new Date().toLocaleDateString("en-US", { month: "long", day: "numeric", year: "numeric" })}.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="legal section-light">
    <div class="container legal-inner">
      <p class="lead">
        We're two dads sharing what we learned the hard way — not doctors, not therapists, not
        financial advisors, and not lawyers. Please read this page before booking anything,
        buying anything, or taking anything we say as gospel.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Not professional advice</h2>
      <p>
        Nothing on this site, in our podcast, our guides, our Prep Kit, our workshops, our
        coaching calls, or the Spit-Up Society community is medical, psychological, legal, or
        financial advice. John and Mike are not licensed physicians, mental health
        professionals, attorneys, or financial advisors, and nothing we publish should replace
        the judgment of one. Abigail's commentary reflects her professional background in
        special education, not a clinical relationship with you. Always talk to your own
        doctor, midwife, therapist, or other qualified professional about your specific
        situation, especially anything related to pregnancy, birth, mental health, or your
        child's health and development.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Personal experience, not guarantees</h2>
      <p>
        Everything we share — the six pillars, the Roadmap, our stories, our frameworks — comes
        from our own experience as dads and from conversations with our community. Your
        situation is your own. We don't guarantee any specific outcome from using our guides,
        attending a workshop, joining a cohort, booking coaching, or being part of the Spit-Up
        Society.
      </p>

      <h2>3. Digital products (Guide &amp; Prep Kit)</h2>
      <p>
        The Free Dad Prep Guide and the Dudela Prep Kit are instant-download digital products.
        Because you get access immediately, digital purchases are generally final and
        non-refundable — but if something's genuinely wrong on our end (a broken download, a
        billing error), email <a href="mailto:dude@thedudelaco.com">dude@thedudelaco.com</a> and
        we'll make it right.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Workshops, cohorts &amp; coaching</h2>
      <p>
        Live sessions (the Before Birth Workshop, the Steady Dad Cohort) and 1:1 coaching are
        booked in advance and may have limited spots. Payment is due at booking unless we tell
        you otherwise. If you need to reschedule, email us as soon as you can and we'll do our
        best to find another time — we don't guarantee a specific makeup slot. These sessions
        are conversations between dads, not therapy or medical treatment.
      </p>

      <h2>5. The Spit-Up Society (membership)</h2>
      <p>
        The Spit-Up Society is a paid monthly membership. You're billed on a recurring basis
        until you cancel; you can cancel at any time and you'll keep access through the end of
        the period you already paid for. We don't prorate partial months.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Merch</h2>
      <p>
        Hats and other physical merch are hand-packed and shipped by us, not a warehouse or
        fulfillment company — please expect shipping to take a little longer than a big-box
        retailer. Joining the merch waitlist doesn't guarantee a specific ship date or that a
        given colorway will still be available when it's your turn.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Intellectual property</h2>
      <p>
        The Dudela name, the six-pillar framework, our guides, and our podcast are ours. You're
        welcome to use what you learn in your own life and to talk about it publicly — please
        just don't resell or republish our materials as your own.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Limitation of liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent allowed by law, The Dudela Co., John, and Mike aren't liable for
        any decision you make based on our content, products, or conversations with us. You're
        responsible for your own choices, and for your family's health and safety decisions in
        particular.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms as the business grows — new products, new formats, new
        policies. We'll update the date at the top of this page when we do.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Questions</h2>
      <p>
        Reach us anytime at <a href="mailto:dude@thedudelaco.com">dude@thedudelaco.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-hero {
    padding: 9rem 0 3rem;
  }
  .page-hero h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 3rem);
    margin: 0.5rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .hero-sub {
    color: var(--text-on-dark-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .legal {
    padding: var(--space-6) 0;
  }
  .legal-inner {
    max-width: 700px;
  }
  .lead {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
  }
  .legal-inner h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .legal-inner p {
    color: var(--text-on-light-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
  }
  .legal-inner a {
    color: var(--rust-600);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
